headline: BofA & Morgan Stanley earnings, Fed Beige Book: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Wednesday, Oct. 14. Bank of America (BAC), Morgan Stanley (MS), United Airlines (UAL), Synchrony Financial (SYF), ASML (ASML), and Abbott Laboratories (ABT) all report earnings results. Federal Reserve commentary is expected from Atlanta Fed President Raphael Bostic, Fed Governor Stephen Miran, and Fed Governor Christopher Waller. The Fed Beige Book will release new economic data in the afternoon. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

content.title: Synchrony and Pumpkin Pet Insurance Partner to Deliver Simple Reimbursements for Pet Owners Through CareCredit
content.summary: Synchrony (NYSE: SYF), a leading consumer financing company, today announced a new partnership with Pumpkin Pet Insurance, to bring its pet health reimbursement solution to even more pet parents. This collaboration provides pet owners with a convenient and simplified way to manage veterinary care costs. Now, pet owners who have both the CareCredit credit card and Pumpkin Pet Insurance can pay for expenses at the point of care and receive their eligible reimbursement directly to their CareCredit

thumbnail.caption: With this offering, Pumpkin Pet Insurance policyholders can utilize their CareCredit credit card to pay for veterinary services upfront at locations in the CareCredit network and select their card to receive payment for their submitted claim.
